<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardened Runtime entitlements for ScrumTeam.app (Developer ID distribution).

  Hardened Runtime itself is enabled by `codesign --options runtime`
  (see scripts/make-app.sh). This file lists the *exceptions* to its
  default restrictions.

  POLICY: start with the minimum and add an exception ONLY after a
  notarization run or runtime test proves it is required (Phase 2).
  Over-broad entitlements weaken security and draw reviewer scrutiny.

  This app is intentionally NOT sandboxed (it embeds a login shell that
  spawns `claude`/`tmux`/`git`/`python3` and reads/writes arbitrary
  files), so there is no `com.apple.security.app-sandbox` key. Child
  processes are exec'd as separate processes, not loaded into this
  process, so library validation is expected to pass without
  `disable-library-validation`.

  CANDIDATE exceptions to evaluate during Phase 2 (add only if proven):
    - com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
        (only if the bundled toolchain dlopens unsigned dylibs INTO
         this process — unlikely, since interpreters run as children)
    - com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
        (only if a future native chat UI uses a JIT)
    - com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables
        (only if we must pass DYLD_* into child processes)
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
</dict>
</plist>
